1
00:01:13,160 --> 00:01:15,560
(8 years ago)

2
00:01:15,560 --> 00:01:16,960
Hey, baby girl!

3
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:19,880
Help! Help!

4
00:01:19,880 --> 00:01:21,120
Hey, hey, hey.

5
00:01:21,680 --> 00:01:23,440
-Where are you going?
-Where are you going?

6
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:24,920
Help!

7
00:01:27,600 --> 00:01:30,000
-Don't hurt me. Don't hurt me.
-Come with me.

8
00:01:31,120 --> 00:01:33,960
I'm begging you. Please let me go.

9
00:02:00,640 --> 00:02:01,760
Hey!

10
00:02:25,880 --> 00:02:26,880
Hey!

11
00:02:45,880 --> 00:02:47,800
Don't harass women again!

12
00:02:49,240 --> 00:02:51,640
-Go!
-Let's go.

13
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,880
Come on.

14
00:02:53,360 --> 00:02:54,360
Let's go.

15
00:02:54,880 --> 00:02:56,040
Let's go.

16
00:03:45,760 --> 00:03:47,040
Can you stand?

17
00:03:53,360 --> 00:03:54,840
Are you hurt anywhere?

18
00:03:58,040 --> 00:03:59,640
How will you get home?

19
00:04:05,360 --> 00:04:07,200
My driver should be around here.

20
00:04:07,800 --> 00:04:10,680
But my phone's dead.

21
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:16,480
Come on.

22
00:04:25,320 --> 00:04:27,000
I'll help you find your car.

23
00:04:55,800 --> 00:04:56,800
Cover yourself.

24
00:04:59,000 --> 00:05:00,240
Your shirt is thin.

25
00:05:38,840 --> 00:05:41,000
Oh! That's my car.

26
00:05:47,320 --> 00:05:49,680
Thank you very much for saving me today.

27
00:05:51,520 --> 00:05:53,880
My name's Ayla. What's yours?

28
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:03,600
Thank you.

29
00:06:56,800 --> 00:06:58,000
Miss Jacket.

30
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:04,240
How is your owner so freaking cool?

31
00:07:04,920 --> 00:07:06,840
She fought off three men.

32
00:07:07,080 --> 00:07:09,440
With an umbrella like this.

33
00:07:10,600 --> 00:07:13,440
How is she pretty, talented and cool?

34
00:07:15,040 --> 00:07:16,440
Only one drawback.

35
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,320
She wouldn't tell me her name.

36
00:07:32,720 --> 00:07:35,360
So how am I going to return this?

37
00:07:38,880 --> 00:07:40,720
I'll probably never see her again.

38
00:07:41,640 --> 00:07:43,160
So you'd better stay with me.

39
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:50,080
I'm talking to a jacket.

40
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,480
Hi, new kid. What's your name?

41
00:08:06,400 --> 00:08:07,800
I'm Ayla.

42
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:09,360
And your first name?

43
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:11,320
Sasina.

44
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:13,480
And your last name?

45
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,920
Ruengkunakorn.

46
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:22,360
Hi, new friend. I'm Khaotu, Suthasinee Sawangkamol.

47
00:08:22,680 --> 00:08:24,240
I've been here since Grade 7.

48
00:08:25,320 --> 00:08:27,560
Nice to meet you, Ayla Sasina.

49
00:08:28,200 --> 00:08:31,280
-Nice to meet...
-If you have questions, feel free to ask me

50
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:33,840
because I know everything

51
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,360
and everyone in this school.

52
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,840
But if grades stress you out,

53
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:40,039
you have nothing to worry about

54
00:08:40,039 --> 00:08:41,559
because I...

55
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,760
get an A in every subject.

56
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,960
Okay, you're good.

57
00:08:48,040 --> 00:08:50,960
Wanna hang out in the classroom or...

58
00:08:52,960 --> 00:08:53,960
Hey!

59
00:08:54,200 --> 00:08:55,200
Hey.

60
00:08:55,880 --> 00:08:56,960
Khaotu.

61
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:59,480
(Don't leave this door open. Always close the door.)

62
00:08:59,480 --> 00:09:00,480
Come on.

63
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,640
Come on.

64
00:09:06,920 --> 00:09:09,080
-So glad we got here in time.
-What's that?

65
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,760
Begin!

66
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,360
It's called kendo.

67
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,440
It's easy to follow. You score for every good hit.

68
00:09:19,840 --> 00:09:21,240
You're awesome!

69
00:09:22,080 --> 00:09:23,440
Wow!

70
00:09:24,320 --> 00:09:26,800
-Wow!
-She's so good.

71
00:09:26,800 --> 00:09:27,920
Resume play!

72
00:10:00,600 --> 00:10:01,440
We've got a winner!

73
00:10:40,480 --> 00:10:41,520
Hey, don't block.

74
00:10:41,520 --> 00:10:43,240
-Sit down, sit down.
-Hey.

75
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,280
That senior.

76
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:48,880
She...

77
00:10:51,840 --> 00:10:53,200
Her name is Tawan.

78
00:10:53,280 --> 00:10:56,480
She's in Grade 12. An outstanding student.

79
00:10:56,480 --> 00:10:57,920
The school president.

80
00:10:58,000 --> 00:11:00,800
And she's our school's kendo champion.

81
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:03,760
She's a three-time champion.

82
00:11:04,560 --> 00:11:05,640
Wow.

83
00:11:06,240 --> 00:11:07,840
Good at school and sports?

84
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:11,000
She's good at everything.

85
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:13,840
And she's pretty.

86
00:11:13,920 --> 00:11:16,160
Cool. The word is "cool."

87
00:11:17,560 --> 00:11:19,920
Anyway, what club are you joining?

88
00:11:24,440 --> 00:11:25,840
(Come Join the Kendo Club)

89
00:11:29,280 --> 00:11:31,560
Are you really sure?

90
00:11:31,560 --> 00:11:32,600
I am.

91
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,440
I want to join the kendo club.

92
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:38,800
But...

93
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:41,800
I think the training is very intense.

94
00:11:42,000 --> 00:11:43,880
I don't think you can handle it.

95
00:11:45,800 --> 00:11:47,320
I'm sure I can handle it.

96
00:11:48,120 --> 00:11:49,800
I'm super ready. I'm all in.

97
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:55,360
Let's see how you do in a tryout.

98
00:11:55,440 --> 00:11:56,920
Are you guys ready?

99
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,440
Yes!

100
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:25,480
By the look of it, that wimp won't make it.

101
00:12:26,280 --> 00:12:28,720
Look at her. She's about to faint.

102
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,400
Let her join if she wanna join.

103
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,600
True.

104
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,280
And who's gonna train her?

105
00:12:40,920 --> 00:12:41,840
I will.

106
00:12:43,960 --> 00:12:45,200
You said it.

107
00:12:45,760 --> 00:12:47,240
You train her.

108
00:12:47,520 --> 00:12:48,520
Deal?

109
00:12:49,320 --> 00:12:50,320
Deal.

110
00:12:52,800 --> 00:12:53,920
All right.

111
00:12:54,200 --> 00:12:55,800
Kid, no more running.

112
00:12:55,880 --> 00:12:57,200
You're in.

113
00:12:57,200 --> 00:12:58,360
Very good effort.

114
00:12:58,800 --> 00:13:00,440
See you tomorrow at the club.

115
00:13:11,920 --> 00:13:13,560
Get up and drink some water.

116
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:20,840
Hey, Tawan.

117
00:13:25,040 --> 00:13:26,200
I feel lightheaded.

118
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:28,960
Are you okay?

119
00:13:37,920 --> 00:13:39,360
Thank you, Tawan.

120
00:13:43,200 --> 00:13:44,720
Do you remember me?

121
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:53,200
You know my name now.

122
00:13:53,480 --> 00:13:54,960
This club is demanding.

123
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:57,400
Yes.

124
00:13:58,640 --> 00:14:00,760
I'll try my best.

125
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:03,360
Thank you for accepting me.

126
00:14:04,960 --> 00:14:05,960
Go.

127
00:14:06,960 --> 00:14:08,000
Time to go home.

128
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,080
See you at the club tomorrow.

129
00:14:12,440 --> 00:14:13,520
Ayla.

130
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,040
Bye-bye, Tawan!

131
00:14:23,360 --> 00:14:25,520
She knows my name.

132
00:14:29,120 --> 00:14:30,760
She knows my name.

133
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,080
Ah!

134
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:58,800
Before we start,

135
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:01,840
I'll show you how we train kendo.

136
00:15:04,240 --> 00:15:06,160
Fight! Begin!

137
00:15:22,400 --> 00:15:24,400
Head! Begin!

138
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,720
Wrist! Begin!

139
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,880
Torso! Begin!

140
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,280
Bow!

141
00:15:50,560 --> 00:15:53,680
You will start from the fundamentals.

142
00:15:54,000 --> 00:15:55,160
Are you ready?

143
00:15:55,240 --> 00:15:56,320
-Yes!
-Yes!

144
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:02,240
Kendo,

145
00:16:02,600 --> 00:16:04,160
the way of the sword,

146
00:16:04,920 --> 00:16:07,760
is based on the samurai swordsmanship.

147
00:16:08,280 --> 00:16:10,720
To train the kendo fighting moves

148
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:14,960
that are fast, forceful and decisive,

149
00:16:15,280 --> 00:16:18,360
deep concentration is required.

150
00:16:32,560 --> 00:16:33,560
Come on.

151
00:16:40,280 --> 00:16:42,480
Come on! Run!

152
00:17:08,440 --> 00:17:09,359
Whoa!

153
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,720
Give us some.

154
00:17:11,839 --> 00:17:13,160
Yeah, take some.

155
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:15,680
-Give me some.
-This one too.

156
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:22,880
Tawan got my gift.

157
00:18:26,240 --> 00:18:27,640
She got my gift.

158
00:18:48,600 --> 00:18:50,200
It's really pouring.

159
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:53,840
Tawan.

160
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:55,960
You haven't left?

161
00:18:57,120 --> 00:19:00,120
Well, I forgot to bring my umbrella.

162
00:19:05,440 --> 00:19:07,280
I forgot my umbrella too.

163
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:09,440
So...

164
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:12,120
why don't we find rain stoppers?

165
00:19:14,280 --> 00:19:15,400
Rain stoppers?

166
00:19:16,480 --> 00:19:17,520
What's that?

167
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:19,680
Let's make rain chasers.

168
00:19:20,480 --> 00:19:21,720
Rain chasers?

169
00:19:40,920 --> 00:19:41,960
Here.

170
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,240
Ooh, there's the sun. Very cool.

171
00:19:59,440 --> 00:20:02,200
The sun is another word for "tawan."

172
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:12,480
Are you drawing the moon?

173
00:20:13,800 --> 00:20:14,920
That's right.

174
00:20:15,920 --> 00:20:17,640
Why the moon?

175
00:20:19,360 --> 00:20:21,360
"Ayla" is another word for the moon.

176
00:20:23,280 --> 00:20:24,280
I see.

177
00:20:31,600 --> 00:20:33,560
The sun and the moon.

178
00:20:34,280 --> 00:20:35,680
Tawan and Ayla.

179
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:39,640
♪ Never once did you notice ♪

180
00:20:39,640 --> 00:20:43,160
♪ What my heart was feeling ♪

181
00:20:43,160 --> 00:20:46,680
♪ When I look at you, my eyes say it all ♪

182
00:20:46,760 --> 00:20:51,600
♪ Waiting only for you to pay me attention ♪

183
00:20:51,680 --> 00:20:58,000
♪ My heart yells every day
But its voice never reaches you ♪

184
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:02,040
♪ I want you to know how long I've kept this in ♪

185
00:21:02,040 --> 00:21:06,680
♪ Do you have any idea ♪

186
00:21:06,680 --> 00:21:09,360
♪ As each minute goes by ♪

187
00:21:09,360 --> 00:21:15,080
♪ How much my heart wants to say I love you? ♪

188
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:20,000
♪ All I know is my heart's stubborn ♪

189
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,360
♪ Even when you ignore me ♪

190
00:21:22,360 --> 00:21:24,040
- ♪ There's pain but also love ♪
- Here we go.

191
00:21:24,040 --> 00:21:28,200
♪ That has never lessened ♪

192
00:21:28,200 --> 00:21:32,200
♪ The closer we are, the further it feels ♪

193
00:21:32,200 --> 00:21:35,640
♪ Never once ♪

194
00:21:35,640 --> 00:21:39,560
♪ Did you notice what ♪

195
00:21:39,560 --> 00:21:42,800
♪ My heart was feeling ♪

196
00:21:43,240 --> 00:21:45,080
♪ When I look at you ♪

197
00:21:45,080 --> 00:21:47,440
- ♪ My eyes say it all ♪
- Look! The rain stops.

198
00:21:47,440 --> 00:21:52,120
- ♪ Waiting only for you to pay me attention ♪
- It really works.

199
00:21:52,120 --> 00:21:57,440
♪ My heart yells every day
But its voice never reaches you ♪

200
00:21:57,440 --> 00:22:00,080
- ♪ I want you to know ♪
- Thank you, rain chasers.

201
00:22:00,080 --> 00:22:02,520
♪ How long I've kept this in ♪

202
00:22:02,520 --> 00:22:07,120
♪ Do you have any idea ♪

203
00:22:07,120 --> 00:22:09,800
♪ As each minute goes by ♪

204
00:22:09,800 --> 00:22:15,320
♪ How much my heart wants to say I love you? ♪

205
00:22:18,960 --> 00:22:20,000
Tawan.

206
00:22:23,560 --> 00:22:25,560
I'm good. Thank you.

207
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,680
-I'll take that.
-Tawan.

208
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,240
Hey.

209
00:22:51,520 --> 00:22:53,240
You think you're so pretty, new kid?

210
00:22:56,000 --> 00:22:59,680
You think Tawan accepts your drink
and you're better than everyone else?

211
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:02,880
You turn your nose up at everyone.

212
00:23:03,560 --> 00:23:04,800
You want a drink?

213
00:23:05,680 --> 00:23:06,400
Here.

214
00:23:07,880 --> 00:23:09,360
I prepared it for you.

215
00:23:09,920 --> 00:23:11,280
But not in a glass.

216
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:13,200
You'll get the whole bucket.

217
00:23:15,280 --> 00:23:17,920
No. No. Don't do it!

218
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:27,560
Tawan.

219
00:23:30,560 --> 00:23:31,920
Tawan.

220
00:23:32,320 --> 00:23:34,400
Why did you have to go this far?

221
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:37,520
I'm sorry. It wasn't meant for you.

222
00:23:37,520 --> 00:23:39,000
It was meant for this new kid.

223
00:23:39,520 --> 00:23:40,600
She just got here.

224
00:23:40,680 --> 00:23:43,040
How could she get this close to you?

225
00:23:43,120 --> 00:23:44,960
I'm the reason, right?

226
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:48,440
I don't approve of this behavior.

227
00:23:50,040 --> 00:23:51,920
Bullying is contemptible

228
00:23:52,280 --> 00:23:53,960
and unacceptable.

229
00:23:54,240 --> 00:23:55,560
No matter to whom.

230
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,360
It breaks my heart

231
00:24:00,080 --> 00:24:02,320
that I'm not setting a good example.

232
00:24:02,600 --> 00:24:04,360
Tawan, no.

233
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:05,920
It's not your fault.

234
00:24:05,920 --> 00:24:08,280
You're very good. You've always been good.

235
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,960
It's our fault.

236
00:24:09,960 --> 00:24:11,440
We're really sorry.

237
00:24:11,640 --> 00:24:12,880
-I'm sorry.
-I'm sorry.

238
00:24:15,120 --> 00:24:16,480
Then let this end here.

239
00:24:16,880 --> 00:24:17,880
I'm asking you.

240
00:24:17,960 --> 00:24:19,160
Of course.

241
00:24:19,360 --> 00:24:21,280
You ask, I obey.

242
00:24:23,360 --> 00:24:24,400
We're good.

243
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:25,880
Huh?

244
00:24:26,760 --> 00:24:29,080
We're good just like that?

245
00:24:29,280 --> 00:24:30,480
Yeah.

246
00:24:30,480 --> 00:24:32,400
Tawan asks, we obey.

247
00:24:40,920 --> 00:24:42,040
Are you okay?

248
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,680
Thank you, Tawan.

249
00:25:21,440 --> 00:25:22,880
For saving me.

250
00:25:25,280 --> 00:25:26,880
You always protect me.

251
00:25:27,200 --> 00:25:29,080
It's like you're my bodyguard.

252
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:35,160
Bodyguard?

253
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,760
I'm expensive.

254
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:40,720
Can you afford me?

255
00:25:46,800 --> 00:25:49,040
Can I ask you something?

256
00:25:52,120 --> 00:25:54,840
You love dancing, right?

257
00:25:59,640 --> 00:26:01,960
Yes, I love dancing.

258
00:26:03,360 --> 00:26:04,920
How did you know?

259
00:26:08,920 --> 00:26:10,120
Well,

260
00:26:10,600 --> 00:26:12,080
I saw you...

261
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:15,480
when you mopped the club floor.

262
00:26:16,920 --> 00:26:18,320
You danced so hard

263
00:26:18,320 --> 00:26:19,320
the floor was clean.

264
00:26:19,400 --> 00:26:20,520
Huh?

265
00:26:26,480 --> 00:26:28,960
Tawan got my gift.

266
00:26:40,920 --> 00:26:42,560
You saw the whole thing?

267
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:45,800
I saw the whole thing.

268
00:26:48,000 --> 00:26:49,520
I saw you were like...

269
00:26:55,440 --> 00:26:57,000
I'm gonna cry.

270
00:26:59,360 --> 00:27:00,560
You saw everything.

271
00:27:13,760 --> 00:27:16,600
Our school has an excellent dance club.

272
00:27:17,040 --> 00:27:19,600
I think you should join it.

273
00:27:21,120 --> 00:27:23,520
Kendo is too much for you.

274
00:27:24,440 --> 00:27:26,480
No, I like kendo.

275
00:27:27,320 --> 00:27:29,120
I like kendo.

276
00:27:31,720 --> 00:27:33,120
I even love it.

277
00:27:40,960 --> 00:27:42,920
You love kendo...

278
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:45,880
more than you love dancing?

279
00:27:49,960 --> 00:27:51,320
I think...

280
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:54,480
that's not true.

281
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,720
Why not?

282
00:27:58,120 --> 00:28:00,600
Do I look that hopeless?

283
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:04,200
Yes.

284
00:28:06,640 --> 00:28:10,240
Tawan, you're not very encouraging.

285
00:28:13,840 --> 00:28:15,280
Just trust me.

286
00:28:15,960 --> 00:28:17,520
Following your heart...

287
00:28:18,400 --> 00:28:19,680
is always better.

